JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Finance Minister, Sfiso Buthelezi, has denied he improperly benefited from Prasa tenders.News24 reported that Buthelezi and his brother Nkanyiso benefited from companies that secured lucrative contracts.READ: Prasa tender scandal: Reports show deeper SOE patronageThe deputy finance minister denied the claims, saying he never influenced any decisions to award any tenders.He said he did not play a role in business relationships between Prasa and the companies. The contracts are said to be worth at least R150-million.Buthelezi chaired the Prasa board when some of the controversial contracts were signed. He says he carries out his duties with utmost integrity.eNCA